70
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:32,610
storing data, moving
data and processing data.

71
00:03:32,610 --> 00:03:35,223
Everything we do can fall
under one of these three.

72
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:38,820
And data is constantly in that flux.

73
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:41,350
It just keeps moving from data at rest

74
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:45,213
to data in transit and data in use.

75
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:48,990
The mechanisms to protect data

76
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:53,730
while the data is at rest and
in transit are fairly mature.

77
00:03:53,730 --> 00:03:56,670
They existed for a long
time, very well-documented.

78
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:58,320
People know how to use it

79
