144
00:07:12,450 --> 00:07:14,400
I think we all agreed,

145
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,140
we're looking to protect sensitive data.

146
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:18,630
So when you're building
specialized capabilities

147
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:20,820
to protect data, it better be the case

148
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:22,020
it is for sensitive data,

149
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:24,630
otherwise it may not be worth the effort.

150
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:27,003
So we know we're talking about
protecting sensitive data.

151
00:07:27,003 --> 00:07:28,563
It's a straightforward answer.

152
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:30,570
When you get into the question

153
00:07:30,570 --> 00:07:32,730
of who you are looking to protect it from,

154
00:07:32,730 --> 00:07:34,893
the answer is oftentimes twofold.

155
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:38,553
Depending on the workload
and the customer,

156
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:44,160
they're at first looking
to protect their content

157
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:47,553
from operators of the cloud
provider, AWS operators.

158
00:07:48,780 --> 00:07:51,000
And depending on the
workload and data types,

159
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,930
sometimes in addition to
protection from AWS operators,

160
00:07:54,930 --> 00:07:57,990
customers want to make
sure they're protecting

161
00:07:57,990 --> 00:08:00,870
that data even from themselves,

162
00:08:00,870 --> 00:08:03,603
from customers' own operators.

163
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,940
To summarize everything I just said,

164
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:10,683
if you weren't fully following it,

165
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:17,330
confidential computing is
the ability to protect data

166
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:20,310
while the data is in use

167
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:23,070
and customers want to protect that data

168
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:25,830
from us and from themselves.

169
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:28,920
That's it, that's the summary
of everything I just said,

170
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,393
protecting data and use.

171
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:34,110
So now let's get into looking at

172
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:37,500
how AWS addresses these considerations.

173
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:40,890
How are we making sure we
are protecting the data

